<%= render :partial => 'layouts/header' %>

<div class="clearfix" style="background: aliceblue;">
	<section class="cd-faq">
		<ul class="cd-faq-categories list-unstyled">
			<li><a class="selected" href="#basics">Basics</a></li>
			<li><a href="#passport">Passport</a></li>
			<li><a href="#mobile">Mobile</a></li>
		</ul> <!-- cd-faq-categories -->

		<div class="cd-faq-items">
			<ul id="basics" class="cd-faq-group list-unstyled">
				<li class="cd-faq-title"><h2>Basics</h2></li>
				<li>
					<a class="cd-faq-trigger" href="#0">What is FitnessPapa?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>FitnessPapa is a monthly membership to the best fitness classes, studios & gyms in your city. There are thousands of classes available to FitnessPapa members, including cycling, Pilates, Yoga, strength training, dance, martial arts, and more.</p>
						<!-- <p>For 1500 rupees a month, FitnessPapa members get 20 classes to studios in the FitnessPapa network. While members can take as many classes per month as they'd like, they can visit the same studio up to 3 times per monthly membership cycle.</p> -->
					</div> <!-- cd-faq-content -->
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">How long is a FitnessPapa membership cycle?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
            <p>Each FitnessPapa cycle is one month in length, and will require repurchase of the passport after end of monthly cycle. For example, if you buy your FitnessPapa on June 3, you'll have to repurchase on July 2. Once your new month starts, you'll be able to re-visit your favorite classes (and also explore new venues!) FitnessPapa does NOT require an annual/long-term commitment.</p>		
					</div>
				</li>
				<!-- <li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">When does my FitnessPapa start?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>FitnessPapa is a monthly recurring membership that activates upon purchasing and automatically renews on the same day of each month.</p>		
					</div>
				</li> -->
				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">How many classes do I get with a FitnessPapa membership?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>You'll be able to take as many classes as offered in the passport. You can visit any studio in the FitnessPapa network up to 3 times per membership cycle.</p>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">Why do I have to rate a class?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>Your reviews will always be completely confidential. We will use your reviews to make future recommendations to you, and to make recommendations to other people like you. And, of course, we will anonymously share your feedback with the studios so that they can keep doing the things you love and make improvements when necessary.</p>		
					</div>
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">Do you have a map of all the venues?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>Please go to FitnessPapa.com and scroll down to the Maps section. You can select your city to see what's offered, and there is also the option to toggle the view so that it is just a list if you prefer!</p>		
					</div>
				</li>


				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">Can I use my FitnessPapa outside of my Home City?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>Absolutely! FitnessPapa you are able to workout in across FitnessPapa Network where we have presence at any time (and for no extra charge) </p>		
					</div>
				</li>



				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">What does "home city" mean?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>Your home city is where you live and where you take the majority of your classes. FitnessPapa allows you to take classes outside of your home city, but it is important to have your account set to the right home city so you hear about events near you!Moving? Wrong home city on your account?
						</p>		
					</div>
				</li>


				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">I have Fitness Studio & how can I partner with FitnessPapa?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>We are adding new workouts and studios every day. If you want to partner with us, please write to us at Partners@fitnesspapa.com, or simply click on the Join As Partners link on our homepage and fill out the form. We would be pleased to discuss the opportunity with you!</p>		
					</div>
				</li>


			</ul> <!-- cd-faq-group -->

			<ul id="passport" class="cd-faq-group list-unstyled">
				<li class="cd-faq-title"><h2>Passport</h2></li>

				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">If a studio has multiple locations, can I take 3 classes per membership cycle at each location?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>If a studio has more than 1 location (even in different cities!), members can go up to 3 times total across all studios. This is the agreement that we have with all of our studios. If you love a studio and want to go more often, you can book directly with the studio!</p>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">How do I reserve a class?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>	
							Reserve a class by clicking on one of the venues, and then selecting the class you would like to attend. Click the “reserve” button next to the class and confirm your reservation, and you’ll be added to the list! You do not need to bring a voucher or print out to class -- just bring Mobile where sms is sent and photo ID.<!-- New classes are available to book every day at noon and most classes are available to reserve on FitnessPapa one week in advance.  -->
						</p>		
					</div>
				</li>

				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">Can I make a last minute reservation?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>Depending on the studio, the deadline to reserve is between 5 minutes to 24 hours in advance of class. We're working with our studios and our engineers to keep the window open as close to class time as possible! </p>		
					</div>
				</li>


				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">Can I reserve a class on a date beyond my current cycle?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>You cannot schedule classes beyond your current cycle. You are required to repurchase passport and you can book classes as usual. <!-- The classes will count towards class allotment for the cycle in which they fall.Please note, if your subscription is cancelled prior to the date of a class you have reserved, that reservation will be cancelled. --></p>		
					</div>
				</li>



				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">Can I make a reservation for a friend using my FitnessPapa?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>FitnessPapa is your own personal, all-access pass to some of the most amazing fitness studios around--when you make a reservation through your FitnessPapa, your own name will show up on the class roster at all of our venues, so they'll be expecting to see you! While FitnessPapa is non-transferable, we know how fun it is to take classes with friends and would definitely recommend encouraging your friends to sign up too!</p>		
					</div>
				</li>


				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">What is the class cancellation policy?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>
						All cancellations must be made atleast before 1 day from date of class. <!-- Late cancellations will result in the loss of a class credit for that studio and will incur a 100 rupees late cancellation fee. If you're not going to be able to make it to a class, please make sure you cancel the class via your FitnessPapa Account page. -->
						</p>
						<!-- <p>If you miss a class that you do not cancel, you will be charged 100 rupees as no-show fee. There's nothing worse than an empty class, so be sure to cancel your reservation in advance so that the studio has the opportunity to give your spot to someone else.
								</p> -->		
					</div>
				</li>

				

				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">How do I know if a class will be the right level for my abilities?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>The FitnessPapa team has tested classes at all of the studios on FitnessPapa to make sure they are suitable for all levels -- from beginners to advanced. We’ve found that in many cases, you get out of class what you put into it, and one class can be both challenging and rewarding to attendees with very different capabilities. Of course, be sure to consult your doctor to make sure you are healthy enough to participate in physical activities!</p>		
					</div>
				</li>


				<li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">The class I want to take is sold out -- what should I do?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>There are a finite number of spaces in each class so we recommend planning early and booking ahead of time to make sure you can get into the class and time you want. We have thousands of classes so try using the search feature to find a similar class in the same neighborhood!</p>
					</div>
				</li>


				<!-- <li>
					<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">Are all of the classes at a studio available to book through FitnessPapa?</a>
					<div class="cd-faq-content">
						<p>We offer full schedules for the majority of our studios, but occasionally studios reserve certain class times only for their members. We are always adding more classes and studios to make sure there are spots available for all our users! Please contact us at support@FitnessPapa.com if you'd like to see the schedule at one particular studio. If there is a studio you'd like to see added to FitnessPapa,</p>		
					</div>
				</li> -->

			</ul>

			<ul class="cd-faq-group list-unstyled" id="mobile">
					<li class="cd-faq-title"><h2>Mobile</h2></li>
					<li>
						<a href="#0" class="cd-faq-trigger">Do you have a Mobile App?</a>
						<div class="cd-faq-content">
							<p>We have a Web & Mobile Site & soon coming with iPhone & Android app.  </p>		
						</div>
					</li>
				</ul>
		</div> <!-- cd-faq-items -->
		<a href="#0" class="cd-close-panel">Close</a>
	</section>
</div>



